    "name": "COU1: Total knee arthroplasty tibial tray contact stress (Class II)",
    "description": "A finite-element model is used to predict peak contact stress on the UHMWPE tibial insert of a total knee replacement implant under ISO 14243-1 physiological loading profiles. Model influence is MODERATE (FE predictions supplement bench testing); decision consequence is MODERATE (incorrect prediction could result in accelerated wear and revision surgery). Model Risk Level 3.",
    "intendedUse": "Use FE simulation to predict peak and mean contact stress on the tibial polyethylene insert across five ISO 14243-1 load cycles. Results must demonstrate contact stress below the material yield threshold and support 510(k) substantial-equivalence claim relative to predicate device.",
